5000|$|<b>Gavioli</b> {{was founded}} in 1806 in Modena, Italy, by Giacomo <b>Gavioli</b> (1786-1875). Giacamo's hobby was the {{development}} of automatic playing musical instruments like bird organs and flute clocks. His son Anselmo was a very clever inventor; he built a large orchestrion organ the [...] "Panharmonico" [...] for the Duke of Modena, who refused to buy the instrument. Ludovico then took it to London and Paris. In 1852 Ludovico <b>Gavioli</b> (1807-1875) moved the business to the trade capital of the organ trade, Paris, France. From 1858 on he started his own organ building company in the Rue d'Aligre. Ludovico had three sons: Anselme, Henry and Claude.|$|E
