5000|$|Born in Recanati, {{the son of}} a {{silversmith}} and a seamstress, Piffarerio {{studied at}} the Brera Academy, where he knew Gino <b>Gavioli,</b> with whom he founded [...] "Gamma Film", a company considered a pioneer in the field of Italian animation. With <b>Gavioli</b> and Gamma Film Piffarerio realized several animation shorts for Carosello, as well as The Long Green Sock (La lunga calza verde), a 1961 medium length film about the history of Italy written by Cesare Zavattini.|$|E
